alerts.text:
From first service until 3am each night from Tuesday 21 March to Thursday 20 April route N40 services will be diverting and missing stops while road closures are in place for Ramadan Night markets around Lakemba Station.


 - Services from the City to East Hills will divert via Haldon St, Lakemba St, King Georges Rd, The Boulevarde then continue as normal. Buses will miss the stop Lakemba Station, The Boulevarde, Stand E (219527), use the alternative stop at Lakemba Station, Haldon St, Stand B (219514).

 - Services from East Hills to the City will divert via King Georges Rd, Lakemba St, Haldon St, The Boulevarde and continue as normal. Buses will miss the stop at Lakemba Station, The Boulevarde (2195118), use the alternative stop on Lakemba Station, Haldon St, Stand A (219515).

Check signs at bus stops for alternative stop locations. For more transport information, see the Ramadan Nights event page.
 
Missed bus stops:


 - Lakemba Station, The Boulevarde, Stand E (Stop ID 219527)

 - Lakemba Station, The Boulevarde (Stop ID 2195118)
alerts.title: Lakemba bus diversions for Ramadan Street Market
